g.text: Measurements of skin hydration and elasticity were performed at baseline (prior to the treatment)
and after one week of treatment. Measurements were taken under controlled temperature (22
5%) conditions, after 30 min of acclimatization. The volunteers were requested not
to apply the gels the morning before the ﬁnal measurement. The use of other products was not allowed
throughout the study, apart from normal hygiene treatment. Skin analyses were performed using
speciﬁc probes of the instrument Soft Plus (Callegari Srl, Parma, Italy). These probes determined skin
hydration by capacity measurements in the range 0–100 u.c. (arbitrary units) with a resolution of 1 u.c.
and 5% precision, while stress/deformation of skin by suction application allowed measurements of
skin elasticity in the range 0–50 u.c. with a resolution of 1 u.c. and 10%precision. Each measurement
